    <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к иран.%i *vi-ba-%i, сращение преверба %ivi-%i с корнем %ibа-%i
        ‘светить’, ‘сиять’ и пр. (ар. %i*bhā-%i, и.е. %i*bha-%i). Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><lang/><w>bā-, vi-bā-</w><gloss><q>сиять</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_BSL"/><biblScope>XXXII 86 сл.</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>bhā-,
            vi-bhā-</w><gloss><q>сиять</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>светить</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="grc"
                ><lang/><w>φαίνω</w><gloss><q>сиять</q></gloss></mentioned> и пр. От этого корня
        происходит и славянская группа: <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/><w>бѣлъ</w></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>белый</w></mentioned> и пр. С формантом %i-nu-%i
        (%ibā-nu-%i) этот корень сохранился в осетинском в значении ‘день’; см. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_bon"/>.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>III
                144</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>17, 34,
                64</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to Iranian %i*vi-ba-%i, it is the fusion of the preverb
        %ivi-%i with the root %ibа-%i ‘to shine’, ‘to beam’ etc. (Aryan %i*bhā-%i, Indo-European
        %i*bha-%i). Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>bā-, vi-bā-</w><gloss><q>to
                shine</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref target="#ref_BSL"/><biblScope>XXXII 86
                сл.</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>bhā-,
                    vi-bhā-</w><gloss><q>to shine</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>to shine</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="grc"
                ><lang/><w>φαίνω</w><gloss><q>to shine</q></gloss></mentioned> etc. The Slavic group
        originates from this root as well: <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/><w>бѣлъ</w></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>белый</w><gloss><q>white</q></gloss></mentioned> etc.
        This root is present in Ossetic with the formant %i-nu-%i (%ibā-nu-%i) in the meaning ‘day’;
        see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bon"/>.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"
                /><biblScope>III 144</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                /><biblScope>17, 34, 64</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
